cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the application of information theory to understand convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also introduces the partial information decomposition (PID) framework, which is a concept from information theory, indicating that cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with image processing and computer vision, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as another possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the training of CNNs, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
